Solar PV technologies can be adapted to customer needs.Solar-powered mini-grids have and continue to be installed in remote islands in Lake Victoria and in the arid and semi-arid areas. The ongoing conversation on the viability of solar technologies for energy access in Kenya is missing one thing; the voice of the ordinary energy consumer, especially the poor and under-served communities that remain in the dark.
 Access to reliable and affordable energy is pivotal to the achievement of the Big 4 Agenda.



