Limited or no access to affordable and appropriate energy solutions significantly compromises the attainment of the Big 4 Agenda, including food and nutrition, security, manufacturing, affordable housing and healthcare.
The government, however, has made great strides towards achieving its energy access goals through the Kenya National Electrification Strategy, which aims to achieve universal electricity service to all households and businesses by 2022.
 Energy access rates stand at 75 per cent, with the recognition of the key role played by off-grid options, particularly mini-grids and stand-alone solar systems that complement grid extension and intensification.



