Solar-powered mini-grids
Solar PV technologies can be adapted to customer needs. They range from pico solar systems that are typically used to provide indoor lighting and mobile charging, to larger and more sophisticated, solar home systems capable of providing energy to power radios, TVs and even fridges. Solar technology is also associated with mini-grid solutions targeted towards remote regions, a sign of substantial demand for energy to power larger equipment.
Solar-powered mini-grids have and continue to be installed in remote islands in Lake Victoria and in the arid and semi-arid areas. They are changing people’s lives, providing utility to numerous households, businesses, and institutions.
The solar sector is one of the strongest in the region with business models and technology innovations such as pay as you go (PayGo), affording low-income earning customers the opportunity to acquire the technology while paying for the energy service in manageable instalments. Solar-powered mini-grid systems are more cost-efficient and environment-friendly than diesel powered generators that were once popularly used for the same service.



